  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Rifling Trunks
---
But now something has happened to make people crane their necks and
stand on tiptoe. "There's a worthy man in such and such a place!" they
cry and, bundling up their provisions, they dash off. At home, they
abandon their parents; abroad, they shirk the service of their ruler.
Their footprints form an unending trail to the borders of the other
feudal lords, their carriage tracks weave back and forth a thousand li
and more. This is the fault of men in high places who covet knowledge.
